A total of 62% of respondents declared themselves &#39;very satisfied&#39; and &#39;satisfied&#39; with the general quality of the couple&#39;s relationship.
&quot;However, 18% show themselves to be &#39;slightly unsatisfied&#39; and &#39;very unsatisfied&#39; in the couple&#39;s relationship, and another 18% declare &#39;suitable&#39;&quot;, is the conclusion of the study, as shown in a press release sent on Tuesday, Ziare .com.
The situation is slightly different when the answers of men and women are analyzed separately.
Thus, 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% suitable, 6% very dissatisfied and 8% slightly dissatisfied.
Regarding women, 33% declared themselves satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very dissatisfied, 14% slightly dissatisfied and 19% chose the appropriate category.
When we look at the degree of satisfaction (positive), we will notice that men are more satisfied.
Regarding the neutral state (suitable), we see a difference of two percent.
&quot;Similarly, in the situation of very dissatisfied, the biggest difference is recorded in the slightly dissatisfied answer, where we see a difference of 6 percent&quot;, the press release states.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romanians (26%) spend an hour or less together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% between two and four hours.
The authors of the study also report that &quot;Romanians feel the need for a little more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), security (20%), new (19%), sex ( 19%), respect 18%, trust 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-knowledge 10% and control 7%&quot;.
The study was conducted by Extreme Training between June 1st and September 1st on 1,369 people, the calculated margin of error being 2.6%.
